# Cinematic Conversation
# A scripted sequence intended for cutscenes — NPC monologue across several
# scenes, no player branching. Each scene's `=>` after the NPC text creates an
# implicit "Continue" advance to the next scene.
#
# Pair with `playback: auto_advance` (per scene) if you want the runtime to
# step forward automatically when the voice-over ends; otherwise the player
# clicks Continue to advance.

NPC: oracle

Oracle:
Long ago, before the iron gates closed for the last time...
playback: auto_advance
=> Beat Two

Scene: Beat Two
Oracle:
...the river ran clean from mountain to sea. Children swam in it.
playback: auto_advance
=> Beat Three

Scene: Beat Three
Oracle:
You have seen the river now. You have travelled through what was lost.
playback: auto_advance
=> Beat Four

Scene: Beat Four
Oracle:
Go. Restore what your fathers broke.
